  {%- comment -%}FAQ{%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What municipal procurement officers ask before sending the PO.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1-800-835-9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll respond in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Which government organizations are OECM-eligible under Agreement 2025-470?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Ontario municipalities (cities, towns, townships, counties, regions), their local boards (police services, public utilities, transit, library boards), conservation authorities, provincial agencies and Crown corporations, and broader-public-sector organizations are OECM-eligible &mdash; they purchase from us under Agreement 2025-470 without an open tender. Federal departments use separate procurement vehicles (PSPC). Not sure where your organization sits? Call <a href="tel:18008359565">1-800-835-9565</a> &mdash; five-minute confirmation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Does your billing meet audit-trail requirements for public-sector procurement?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. Every line-item quote carries the OECM agreement number (2025-470), your PO reference field, and SKU-level pricing that matches the OECM catalog. Invoices reproduce the PO 1:1 by SKU with agreement-number reference. Procurement portals (Ariba, Bonfire, Biddingo, Merx) and MFR-compliant procurement workflows are supported on request.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can you handle multi-department or multi-site municipal rollouts?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; municipal multi-site is most of our government work. We quote per-site or per-department with a master roll-up against your PO, sequence installs against your operational calendar (after-hours, weekend, phased department-by-department), and ship to a single warehouse or direct-to-site. Split billing across departments accommodated on request. One Ontario project manager owns the file across every location.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What&rsquo;s the lead time on a council-chamber refresh or admin-office build-out?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Most in-stock admin and task seating ships within 2&ndash;3 weeks of PO. Custom-configured pieces &mdash; council-chamber tables, COM-upholstered chairs, secure-records storage &mdash; are typically 6&ndash;10 weeks. We confirm lead time per line on every quote and sequence the install against your council schedule or municipal renovation window.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">05</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do you accept POs, NET-30, and municipal procurement portal billing?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; municipal POs and NET-30 are standard. Procurement-portal formats (Ariba, Bonfire, Biddingo, Merx) and MFR/PSPC-compliant invoice templates supported. We can provide a proforma invoice if your finance office requires it before PO issuance. For OECM orders the agreement number appears on the quote so your procurement office processes it cleanly.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">06</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Does every quote include a free space plan for council chambers and service areas?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; free 2D layout on every project. Especially useful for council chambers, public-facing service counters, and committee rooms where sightlines, accessibility (AODA compliance), and public-flow constraints matter. Send your floor plan (AutoCAD, PDF, or sketch). On-site measure available when needed.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">07</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can you install during business hours without disrupting public services?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; after-hours, weekend, and phased department-by-department installs are standard for occupied government buildings. Our own install crew handles uncrating, assembly, levelling, placement, and removal of old furniture so the space is service-ready by Monday morning. For phased renovations we sequence delivery windows with your facilities team before the first truck arrives.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

